Serializable
public class InstanceOfMVELFilter<T>
extends MVELFilter<T>

An MVELFilter that conveniently checks the current item to see if it is an instance of a specified Class before applying further MVEL-based filters to it.

Author:
Laird Nelson

accept

public boolean accept(T item,
                      Map<Object,Object> variables)
Returns true if the supplied item is non-null and has a Class that compares properly with the Class supplied at construction time.

Class comparison is controlled by the return value of the isExact() method. If it is true, then the supplied item must have a Class that is equal to the Class supplied at construction time. If it is false, then the supplied item must merely be an instance of that Class.

Overrides:
accept in class MVELFilter<T>
Parameters:
item - the Object to be accepted; may be null in which case false will be returned
variables - a Map of variables that may be populated by the MVEL expression supplied at construction time
Returns:
true if the execution of the MVEL expression associated with this MVELFilter returned an Object equal to Boolean.TRUE when evaluated against the supplied item; false otherwise
See Also:
isExact(), InstanceOfMVELFilter(Class, boolean, String)
